
[1]mastich

   MAS'TICH, n. [L. mastiche.]

   1. A resin exuding from the mastic-tree, a species of Pistacia, and
   obtained by incision. It is in white farinaceous tears, of a faint
   smell, and is used as an astringent and an aromatic. It is used also as
   an ingredient in drying varnishes.

   2. A kind of mortar or cement.
